# LEAN Domain
# ===========
# Rules for LEAN-GSD workflow. Activated when working with plans, phases, and roadmaps.

LEAN_RULE_0=Follow PLAN.md as the executable prompt — do not deviate beyond deviation rules R1-R4
LEAN_RULE_1=Each plan targets ~50% context budget — max 2-3 tasks per plan
LEAN_RULE_2=Atomic commits per task — never git add . — only explicit file staging
LEAN_RULE_3=Check <boundaries> section before modifying any file — protected files are non-negotiable
LEAN_RULE_4=Acceptance criteria (AC-N) define "done" — task completion alone is insufficient
LEAN_RULE_5=Update STATE.md after every phase transition and significant decision
LEAN_RULE_6=R4 deviations (architectural changes) require STOP and user approval — never auto-proceed
LEAN_RULE_7=Verify all claimed artifacts exist on disk before marking SUMMARY.md complete
LEAN_RULE_8=Subagent executors get fresh 200k context — keep plans small enough to execute cleanly
LEAN_RULE_9=After APPLY, reconcile plan vs actual — compare acceptance criteria against real artifacts (UNIFY)
